&lt;p&gt;
	Johnson County&lt;br /&gt;
	Mountain City, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Beautiful scenery&lt;br /&gt;
	- No restaurants, no apparent history&lt;br /&gt;
	- No culture&lt;br /&gt;
	- Since there isn&amp;#39;t an easy route to the city from the interstate, the area is isolated from commerce opportunities.&lt;br /&gt;
	- Geographically, being in a small valley reduces the amount of land available for housing and factories. Both are needed for sustaining population of any significance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Sullivan County&lt;br /&gt;
	Blountville, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Ok history&lt;br /&gt;
	- Scenery not as great&lt;br /&gt;
	- Decent culture&lt;br /&gt;
	- Bristol and Kingsport dominate the area now... there&amp;#39;s not much effort in making Blountville better&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Carter County&lt;br /&gt;
	Elizabethton, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great history&lt;br /&gt;
	- Scenery not as great&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great culture&lt;br /&gt;
	- Close enough to ETSU that professors (and potentially students) could live here and commute north.&lt;br /&gt;
	- Interstate access (I-26) allows multiple big box stores, grocery stores, and a super-Walmart.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Washington County&lt;br /&gt;
	Jonesborough, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Rich history&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great scenery&lt;br /&gt;
	- Good culture&lt;br /&gt;
	- Abundance of 1700s buildings. Many original to the square.&lt;br /&gt;
	- Close proximity to Johnson City means that there&amp;#39;s not much located in Jboro. For grocerey, Walmart, etc you have to make the 10 minute drive to Johnson City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Unicoi County&lt;br /&gt;
	Erwin, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great history&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great scenery&lt;br /&gt;
	- Ok culture. Art gallery and multiple libraries.&lt;br /&gt;
	- Abundance of old buildings in historic district. Most are restored and well kept.&lt;br /&gt;
	- Isolated enough that it has grocery, Walmart, and TSC. Wouldn&amp;#39;t have to leave the area for staples of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Greene County&lt;br /&gt;
	Greeneville, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great history&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great culture&lt;br /&gt;
	- Good scenery&lt;br /&gt;
	- Very large downtown area for a city of its size. Many businesses still active, but transiition is apparent.&lt;br /&gt;
	- Convention center / restaurant is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Hawkins County&lt;br /&gt;
	Rogersville, TN&lt;br /&gt;
	- Great scenery&lt;br /&gt;
	- Small-town culture&lt;br /&gt;
	- Good history&lt;/p&gt;
